irionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tukka>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/6/03 8:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3987.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/glowhand.jpg height=44 width=44></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Master looters who suck.</span><hr size=1> I was invited into a Bastion of Thunder group today.  I think the group had just lost someone and I was filling a vacant spot.  One of the characters in our group was doing all the looting, so I figured he was MLing.<br>
<br>
Right off the bat, I don't really like master looting in pickup groups.  First of all, you often don't know the people you're grouping with, and if they're to be trusted.  Second, it's inconvenient even if you are trusting, because oftentimes in pickup groups, people come and go, and trying to evenly figure out how to split the loot in those situations can be more trouble than it's worth.<br>
<br>
However, when I'm the newcomer in an already formed group, I'm not inclined to tell the group to stop doing what they've been doing, as that can create its own complications.<br>
<br>
So we're in this group, and we're pulling from the earth wing to the four-way junction.  Early on, a spectral parchment drops and is looted by the MLer.  It's possible that I'm the only one (besides the looter) who noticed it, because nobody said anything.  At this point I had all but one of my level 63/64, so I don't get all excited over a ML drop, so I didn't celebrate it.<br>
<br>
Later we move to the table/forge room and start clearing there.  The first named we killed there dropped a thunderous ring a spirit, and the next one we killed dropped the drums and a spectral parchment.  At this point someone asks if we should roll, and I suggest we wait until the end (or until someone leaves) to roll since we hadn't rolled on anything up to that point yet.  They accept, we fight some more and kill another named and get another ring.<br>
<br>
At this point the cleric has to leave and she asks for the jord meat we'd collected up to that point.  Nobody answers her at first, as we're talking about rolling on the stuff we got.  The cleric starts getting impatient, repeatedly asking for the meat, and someone else in the group says &quot;Give her the meat already&quot;, and the MLer says &quot;I destroyed it.&quot;  At first we're not sure if he's joking or not.  He gives her 1 jord meat.  She asks for the rest, and he says he destroyed it.  Okay, I could see how a newbie to the zone may make that mistake (even though the cleric claims she said up front at the beginning that she wanted the meat, and the MLer was level 65).<br>
<br>
So then we got to the loot we're rolling on.  I say, &quot;Okay, so we've got two rings, a drum, and 2 (or was it 3) spectral parchments?&quot; (I wasn't sure if two of the nameds had dropped parchments or just one, but I distinctively remembered that two drops).  The MLer says &quot;Only one spectral&quot;.  I ask him to check his inventory again.  He says &quot;No, just one spectral and the EP we got earlier&quot;.<br>
<br>
Despite my insistence that two SPs had been looted, the MLer maintained that he only had the one.  Anyway, we rolled on the stuff and I won the SP that he did concede that.  However, the MLer (a warrior) rolled on the parchment despite the fact that I asked at one point (not during a fight or anything, when nobody was busy or AFK)  if we were doing NGB, one person replied &quot;Yes.&quot; and nobody objected.  Anyway, he got the highest roll and when I noticed that we were moving on to roll for other stuff and I hadn't yet been handed my parchment, I asked &quot;I won the parchment, didn't I?&quot; and he says &quot;I rolled higher, though. ;P&quot;--again, he might have been joking/teasing, but given the rest of his behavior I'm not inclined to give him the benefit of the doubt.  Someone remarks &quot;You can't use it&quot; and he gives me the parchment without any more of a struggle.<br>
<br>
By the way, I checked the log file and he did indeed loot two parchments (one at 15:31:33 and the other at 18:04:00), so it's not just my faulty memory at work here.<br>
<br>
So the only conclusion I can come to is that A) he destroyed the parchment, thinking it was only ethereal (still a really stupid thing to do, as you will sometimes find someone in BoT who wants the EPs if not for themselves, for a friend or alt), B) it was in his inventory and he just didn't do a thorough check of all of his bags despite my insistence that an additional SP was looted or C) He was a greedy fucking liar.<br>
<br>
I'm leaning towards C.<br>
<br>
I'm not posting the name though, since most of you don't know me well enough to trust my word over his.  My friends who do know/trust me will be receiving a warning about the greed and/or incompetence of this individual.<br>
<br>
The lesson I've learned here is to be very wary MLing in pickup groups and to speak up &quot;for the record&quot; whenever I notice someone loot something of value.<br>
<br>
A lesson for all you would-be MLers out there, though:<br>
<br>
1) Don't be a greedy prick.<br>
<br>
2) If you don't know what something is for or if it has any value, ASK the group or look it up before destroying it.<br>
<br>
3) Pay attention to what you loot and where you put it, and if someone asks you to check your inventory for an item, do a proper job of it.<br>
<br>
Here's a couple others, peeves of mine that I noticed in my MLer that are less serious, but still somewhat annoying:<br>
<br>
4) Don't volunteer yourself as MLer if you have a common lore item that drops in the area banked.  The MLer should be able to keep the area clear of corpses by themselves if possible.<br>
<br>
5) When your group drops a named NPC, don't stand crouched over the corpse for 20 seconds making silly remarks without looting the corpse or even saying what the mob had, especially when you're the MT and the enchanter has a mob mezzed.<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p>--Velsor<br>
Shadow Knight of Cazic-Thule<br>
Seeker of the Dark Truth<br>
