<br>
In places like BoT, I really think that one of the better policies that might serve is the old fashioned &quot;alpha loot&quot; or some variant on it.  So you can loot until you get a diamond/raw diamond/whatever, then you don't loot (except to clear corpses, ect.) until everyone else gets a gem.<br>
<br>
Personally that's the rule I tend to follow when I'm in a group that's not MLing, even if I don't tell the group that's what I'm doing.  I get my gem, and wait until I see 5 or more gems drop before looting again, unless a corpse has been lying around for a pull or two without anybody looting it, then I'll play garbageman, and if it gets me paid, cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I try not to be too greedy, but people can't be too generous either.  If you're about to leave a group and you haven't looted any diamonds or good vendor loot yet, speak up and chances are there will be at least one generous individual in the group willing to part with one of theirs. <p>--Velsor<br>
