<br>
Done Alpha looting. Problem there is forgetting who was next to loot.<br>
<br>
Done ML. Works if the groups going to start and end together so all can get a fair split. Or you know the group and know you'll get your fair share later.<br>
<br>
Best method of looting? Depends on who your with and if you trust them. For a pickup group, Alpha's the best looting bases with a condition to 'special' loot.<br>
<br>
Alpha looted recently and the leader declared that gems would be rolled for - but once you won a gem you didn't roll again until everyone had won a gem. Same applied for kit drops. Everything else went to the looter with auto split off. Nice additional rule, though, was Clerics were to loot twice every other round to cover for regents. Something I think most people forget - that Temperance, Symbol or Virtue has cost the Cleric a gem - commonly a Peridot worth 11pp approx. As they get pestered to cast these on the MA and SA, and even on the puller, the cleric's often out of pocket to start with. Oh, and Peridots were split between clerics and were not counted towards loot in addition to the loot twice rule. I expect that, in an area that was richer in drops, though, that rule might have been altered.<br>
<br>
Then again - the group was mostly known to each other, so there was an intrisic level of trust there.<br>
<br>
Usually wind up as Master Looter - or at least the seller (tend to have the highest CHA, and faction). It is *very* important you trust the person selling / splitting.<br>
<br>
But the simple rule is - when joining a group, check what the loot policy is. If there's something specific you're looking for - say so. Speak early on, or live with the consequences. After all - what if that Warrior was the only person in the group who *wanted* to loot? If everyone else was full or near max weight? Unless you speak out, you'll not know and therefor not be able to judge if you even want to stick with the group (Would you join a pick-up group where all Blue Diamonds were going to one person, but that person also got an even split of all other loot?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baldisking>Baldisking</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/7/03 10:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3987.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Master looters who suck.</span><hr size=1> /agree   I've seen some greedy bastards out there.<br>
