Velsor, whoever looted for you gives us proper ML'ers a bad name :P<br>
<br>
Some of us keep tabs and do our best to loot divy fairly. I almost ALWAYS roll on good loot right away though so no one forgets at all, as we get it. Easier that way.<br>
<br>
(unless its a raid, can't roll during a raid of course)<br>
<br>
Out of the loot when I ML my consideration is first: Cleric, to compensate cleric first for dots spent. Second would be to do the rolls, third would be to divide everything else up fairly. If there's some special thing only a baker would want or whatever, folks get asked if so and so can have. (Like who wants the durned hobgoblin meat, or the hero parts, or whatever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
If someone leaves, they usually get loot from me later as I write down what we had up until that moment and then start fresh counter for the 'new' group. I keep a notebook beside me and if its a pickup group what changes rapidly, then I keep copious notes to make sure eveyrone gets treated fairly.<br>
<br>
sometimes I've divvied up the saleable loot amongst folks leaving keeping some for the rest of the group. Sometimes it may not be exactly perfect, but its not perfect in alpha loot either, because in alpha loot sometimes you get an empty corpse, and many groups still consider that 'you' looted, on to the next!<br>
